   {:e #blake3 "7ceee7a0a7fe29c82f3bc9a133a72bda4a4a4ff3cf5c51a27718ca8b33dd3379" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: observe.rs:601 uses 'let _ = live.write_tx(&cce_tx)' — silently discards write failures for embedding, concept assignment, and entity link datoms. The main observation datoms are written with proper error propagation, but the CCE follow-up transaction is fire-and-forget. On disk-full or permission errors, the observation appears to succeed but loses all CCE metadata. APPROACH: Replace 'let _ = live.write_tx(&cce_tx);' with 'live.write_tx(&cce_tx)?;'. One-character fix. ACCEPTANCE: (A) No 'let _ = ' on any write_tx call in observe.rs. (B) All existing tests pass. (C) If write_tx fails, the observe command returns an error to the caller. CONSIDERATIONS: This surfaces errors that were previously silent. Users may see new errors on disk-full scenarios. This is correct behavior — silent data loss is worse than a visible error. DEPENDS-ON: nothing. FILE: crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs:601" :op :assert}
